==English==
===Etymology===
[[choke]] + [[-er]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A piece of [[jewelry]]/[[jewellery]], worn as a [[necklace]], tight to the throat.
# One who chokes ([[strangle]]s) another person.
# One who operates the [[choke]] of an [[engine]] during [[ignition]].
#(''slang'') Any [[disappoint]]ing or [[upset]]ting circumstance.
#:''I lost £100 on the horses today &mdash; what a choker!''

====Synonyms====
*(''one who chokes another''): [[strangler]]
*(''slang: disappointing or upsetting circumstance''): [[bummer]], [[downer]], [[pisser]]

